 {"id":"asupersync-8xn","title":"Implement two-phase watch channel for state broadcasting","description":"## Purpose
Implement a cancel-safe watch channel - a single-value channel where receivers see the latest value. Essential for configuration propagation, state sharing, and shutdown signals.

## Watch Semantics
- Single producer broadcasts state changes
- Multiple receivers observe latest value
- Receivers can wait for changes
- No queue - only latest value matters

## Two-Phase Watch Model

```rust
pub fn watch<T: Clone>(initial: T) -> (Sender<T>, Receiver<T>);

pub struct Sender<T> {
    inner: Arc<WatchInner<T>>,
}

pub struct Receiver<T> {
    inner: Arc<WatchInner<T>>,
    seen_version: u64,  // Track which version we've seen
}

struct WatchInner<T> {
    value: RwLock<(T, u64)>,  // (value, version)
    notify: Notify,           // Wake waiters on change
}
```

### Sender API
```rust
impl<T: Clone> Sender<T> {
    /// Send new value, notifying all receivers.
    pub fn send(&self, value: T) -> Result<(), SendError> {
        // Acquire write lock
        // Update value and increment version
        // Notify all waiters
    }

    /// Modify value in place.
    pub fn send_modify<F: FnOnce(&mut T)>(&self, f: F) {
        // Acquire write lock
        // Apply modification
        // Increment version
        // Notify waiters
    }

    /// Get reference to current value.
    pub fn borrow(&self) -> Ref<'_, T>;

    /// Subscribe creates new receiver.
    pub fn subscribe(&self) -> Receiver<T>;
}
```

### Receiver API
```rust
impl<T: Clone> Receiver<T> {
    /// Wait for a new value (change since last seen).
    pub async fn changed(&mut self, cx: &mut Cx<'_>) -> Result<(), RecvError> {
        // Loop: check version > seen_version
        // If yes: update seen_version, return Ok
        // If no: wait on notify, respecting cancellation
    }

    /// Get current value (may not have changed).
    pub fn borrow(&self) -> Ref<'_, T>;

    /// Get cloned value.
    pub fn borrow_and_clone(&self) -> T;

    /// Mark current value as seen.
    pub fn mark_seen(&mut self);
}
```

## Common Patterns

### Configuration Updates
```rust
let (config_tx, config_rx) = watch::channel(Config::default());

// Reader task
scope.spawn(cx, async move |cx| {
    loop {
        config_rx.changed(cx).await?;
        let config = config_rx.borrow_and_clone();
        apply_config(config);
    }
});

// Config updater
config_tx.send(new_config)?;
```

### Shutdown Signal
```rust
let (shutdown_tx, shutdown_rx) = watch::channel(false);

// Worker checks for shutdown
scope.spawn(cx, async move |cx| {
    loop {
        select\! {
            _ = shutdown_rx.changed(cx) => {
                if *shutdown_rx.borrow() { break; }
            }
            _ = do_work(cx) => {}
        }
    }
});

// Trigger shutdown
shutdown_tx.send(true)?;
```

## Cancellation Handling
- `changed()` is cancel-safe - can abort wait cleanly
- Receiver state (seen_version) not corrupted by cancellation
- Can resume waiting after cancellation

## Why Two-Phase Here?
Watch doesn't need full two-phase on send (atomic update), but receiver-side wait is cancel-safe:
- Cancel during `changed()`: clean abort, version not updated
- Resume: continue waiting for same version

## Invariant Support
- **No data loss**: Latest value always available
- **Cancel-safety**: Wait operations are interruptible
- **Multiple receivers**: Clone on subscribe

## Testing Requirements
1. Single receiver sees updates
2. Multiple receivers see same updates
3. `changed()` only returns on new value
4. Cancel during `changed()` wait
5. Sender dropped (receivers get error)
6. Version tracking correctness

## References
- asupersync_plan_v4.md: §6.5 Two-Phase Operations (receiver-side)
- tokio::sync::watch (reference implementation)
- Broadcast channels in other frameworks

## Acceptance Criteria
- Watch updates are delivered without silent loss under cancellation (protocol-defined behavior).
- Receiver acks (if used) are linear and enforced by the obligation registry.
- Unit/E2E tests cover cancellation while waiting and while processing updates.
